Others: Milwaukee Bucks moved Khris Middleton to the bench prior to their game against the San Antonio Spurs on January 9, 2025.
Middleton scored just eight points against the Spurs, averaging 12.8 points this season, which is his second-lowest total in his career.
Middleton has missed many games due to recovery from bilateral ankle surgery, impacting his lateral movement on defense and explosion around the rim.
